verbs.description: outstunt (third-person singular simple present outstunts, present participle outstunting, simple past and past participle outstunted)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To perform more or better stunts than.
examples: Boelcke, well aware of the slimness of his chances for surviving the encounter, seeing that his Fokker could neither outrace nor outstunt the splendid new French pursuit machine, decided to risk everything on one final subterfuge.
